{
  "info": {
    "name": "Veilix (DVS) Documentation",
    "description": "Complete API documentation for the Veilix DVS Backend\n\n## Base URL\n`http://localhost:3001/api/v1`\n\n## Authentication\nMost endpoints require a JWT token. After login, add the token to the `Authorization` header as `Bearer <token>`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "12345678"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register User",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "    pm.test(\"User registered successfully\", function () {",
                  "        pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePassword123!\",\n  \"username\": \"testuser\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/register",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "register"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Register a new user account. An OTP will be sent to the provided email for verification.\n\n**Request Body:**\n- `email` (string, required): User's email address\n- `password` (string, required): User's password\n- `username` (string, required): Unique username\n\n**Responses:**\n- `201`: User registered successfully\n- `400`: Invalid input data\n- `409`: Email already exists"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify Email",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"otp\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-email",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "verify-email"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Verify email address using OTP sent during registration.\n\n**Request Body:**\n- `email` (string, required): User's email address\n- `otp` (string, required): 6-digit OTP code\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Email verified successfully\n- `400`: Invalid or expired OTP\n- `404`: User not found"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"authToken\", jsonData.token);",
                  "    pm.test(\"Token saved to environment\", function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(jsonData.token).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePassword123!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Login with email and password. Returns JWT token for authenticated requests.\n\n**Request Body:**\n- `email` (string, required): User's email\n- `password` (string, required): User's password\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Login successful, returns user data and JWT token\n- `401`: Invalid credentials\n- `400`: Missing email or password\n\n**Note:** The JWT token is automatically saved to environment variable `authToken`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/profile",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "profile"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Get current user's profile information.\n\n**Authentication:** Required (Bearer Token)\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Profile retrieved successfully\n- `401`: Unauthorized or invalid token\n- `404`: Profile not found"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"newemail@example.com\",\n  \"username\": \"newusername\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/update",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "update"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Update user profile information.\n\n**Authentication:** Required (Bearer Token)\n\n**Request Body:**\n- `email` (string, optional): New email address\n- `username` (string, optional): New username\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Profile updated successfully\n- `401`: Unauthorized\n- `500`: Update failed"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Reset Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"newPassword\": \"NewSecurePassword456!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "reset-password"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Reset user password.\n\n**Request Body:**\n- `email` (string, required): User's email\n- `newPassword` (string, required): New password\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Password reset successfully\n- `400`: Missing required fields\n- `404`: User not found"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/logout",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "logout"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Logout current user.\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Logged out successfully"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Authentication endpoints for user registration, login, profile management, and password reset."
    },
    {
      "name": "Breach Checking",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Check Email for Breaches",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"lastCheckId\", jsonData.data.checkId);",
                  "    pm.test(\"Email check successful\", function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(jsonData.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/breach/check-email",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "breach",
                "check-email"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Check if an email address has been compromised in any known data breaches.\n\n**Authentication:** Required (Bearer Token)\n\n**Request Body:**\n- `email` (string, required): Email address to check\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Check completed successfully\n- `400`: Invalid email format\n- `401`: Unauthorized\n- `500`: Check failed\n\n**Rate Limiting:** This endpoint is rate-limited to prevent HIBP API abuse. Wait 6-7 seconds between requests.\n\n**Note:** The `checkId` is automatically saved for use with the Report endpoint."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Check Password for Breaches",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/breach/check-password",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "breach",
                "check-password"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Check if a password has been exposed in data breaches using k-anonymity model.\n\n**Authentication:** Required (Bearer Token)\n\n**Request Body:**\n- `password` (string, required): Password to check\n\n**Security:** The password is hashed locally and only the first 5 characters of the hash are sent to the API. The full password never leaves your server.\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Check completed\n- `400`: Password is required\n- `401`: Unauthorized\n- `500`: Check failed\n\n**No Rate Limiting:** Password checks don't count toward HIBP rate limits."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Batch Check Emails",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"emails\": [\n    \"test1@example.com\",\n    \"test2@example.com\",\n    \"test3@example.com\"\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/breach/check-batch",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "breach",
                "check-batch"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Check multiple email addresses for breaches in a single request.\n\n**Authentication:** Required (Bearer Token)\n\n**Request Body:**\n- `emails` (array, required): Array of email addresses (max 10)\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Batch check completed\n- `400`: Invalid input or too many emails\n- `401`: Unauthorized\n- `500`: Check failed\n\n**Rate Limiting:** This endpoint will take time to complete as it respects HIBP rate limits (6-7s delay between each email check).\n\n**Max emails per request:** 10"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Endpoints for checking emails and passwords against the Have I Been Pwned database."
    },
    {
      "name": "Reports & History",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Breach History",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/breach/history?limit=20&offset=0",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "breach",
                "history"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "limit",
                  "value": "20",
                  "description": "Number of records to return (default: 20)"
                },
                {
                  "key": "offset",
                  "value": "0",
                  "description": "Number of records to skip (default: 0)"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Get paginated history of all breach checks performed by the user.\n\n**Authentication:** Required (Bearer Token)\n\n**Query Parameters:**\n- `limit` (number, optional): Records per page (default: 20)\n- `offset` (number, optional): Records to skip (default: 0)\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: History retrieved successfully\n- `401`: Unauthorized\n- `500`: Failed to fetch history"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Generate Breach Report",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/breach/report/{{lastCheckId}}",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "breach",
                "report",
                "{{lastCheckId}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Generate a detailed breach report for a specific check.\n\n**Authentication:** Required (Bearer Token)\n\n**Path Parameters:**\n- `checkId` (string, required): UUID of the breach check\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Report generated successfully\n- `401`: Unauthorized\n- `404`: Check not found\n- `500`: Report generation failed\n\n**Note:** Use the `checkId` returned from the \"Check Email\" endpoint. It's automatically saved to `lastCheckId` environment variable."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Statistics",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/breach/stats",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "breach",
                "stats"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Get comprehensive statistics about user's breach checks.\n\n**Authentication:** Required (Bearer Token)\n\n**Responses:**\n- `200`: Statistics retrieved successfully\n- `401`: Unauthorized\n- `500`: Failed to fetch statistics\n\n**Returns:**\n- Total breach checks performed\n- Total breaches found\n- Checks in last 30 days\n- Number of compromised passwords\n- Recent activity"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Endpoints for viewing breach history, generating reports, and accessing statistics."
    },
    {
      "name": "Documents",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Upload Document",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{authToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/document/upload",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "document",
                "upload"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Upload a single document file. Requires authentication (Bearer token). Use multipart/form-data with field name 'file'. Supported types: PDF and common images."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Document upload endpoints"
    }
  ],
